<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-004-266 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 614 432</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Dec 1991 v16 n13 p222(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Presentation Team 2.0. (Software Review ) (one of 12 evaluationsof presentation software packages)(Solutions Focus/PresentationSoftware) (Evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Diehl, Stanford.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Digital Research Inc's Presentation Team 2.0, priced at $495, isactually based on the GEM graphical interface, although it isweighed against the DOS-based packages for the purposes of thisreview.andP;  A run-time version of the GEM interface and the Hijaakfile-conversion program are bundled with Presentation Team.andP;  Boththe ruler and the grid supplied with the layout tools arecustomizable, and there is a full set of alignment tools.andP;  Thereis a duplicate menu option, but it does not function as astep-and-repeat tool.andP;  There is a strong set of text tools and thegraphing module covers the basics, but its operation is not alwaysintuitive and it would not import a Lotus 1-2-3 file.andP;  There isalso no direct method for importing raw ASCII files; a utilitydisk obtained from Digital must be used for that purpose.andP;  Theslide show function also needs improvement.andP;  Overall, while a cutabove most DOS packages, Presentation Team 2.0 does not come up tothe standards of the Windows packages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Research Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Presentation Team 2.0 (Presentation software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationComparisonPresentation Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>